Ingredients

125g  Butter
125g  caster sugar
2     eggs
125g  plain flour
3.5g  baking powder
Some  Milk

Steps

1 - Mix the butter and sugar in to a pasty mess
2 - Crack in the eggs and bean in to a slightly gooey pasty mess
3 - Add flour and fold in
4 - Add a little milk until it has a almost slimy texture
5 - Line a cake tin with thing to stop the cake sticking (baking parchment)
6 - Pour cake mix into tin
7 - Cook at 180 degrees C for about 20mins
8 - Place on a rack to cool
9 - Eat
